OL,6,F"Several students in the class had
OL,7,Fpersonal stories about bullying, and
OL,8,Fthey wanted to use film to turn
OL,9,Fsomething difficult into something
OL,10,Fpowerful. From there, the creativity
OL,11,Ftook off," he said.
OL,13,FHe said "it was an amazing experience.
OL,14,FThe main thing for us was that we are
OL,15,Fa special needs school and we got
OL,16,Fnominated for a mainstream award, that
OL,17,Fwas the big thing for us."
